arrings ~ pretty good stats, but not fantastic. I have been thinking of changing to Sonic Wolf Claw earrings for a while now, and had auctioned to buy one. Anyway, Srir sees my earrings and says he really needs them for the effect they have (mana preservation I). He wants to trade my earring for a Sonic Wolf Claw one he has. This seems good to me ~ the cougar claw is cheaper anyway, and what does a monk need Mana Preservation for?<br>&quot;OK&quot; I tell him<br>So Srir tells me he'll have to go get it, but since we're still fighting, can he borrow the cougar claw &lt;WARNING BELLS NOW RINGING&gt;<br>&quot;Umm, there's a bank right here in the zone, just run get it&quot; (Duh ~ who fights in HHK and doesn't know there's a bank)<br>So he says,&quot;OK, after this fight we'll go get it.&quot;<br>So we run up to the bank, and he says, “give me the cougar claw earring.&quot; So I hand it to him, but (of course) I haven't hit trade yet, because he still hasn't given me his earring.<br>&quot;Just hit trade,” he says, &quot;I need to run to Luclin to get yours for you. It will take 20 minutes or so&quot; &lt;ALARM ! ! DANGER ! ! &gt;<br>&quot;Nah ~ Luclin is easy enough to get to (Just a bit of a run to the NK spires from HHK) I'll go with you&quot;<br>At this point he decides he doesn't want to trade any more. Huh, go figure. He has also disbanded the group (Guess we were done fighting so we could go to Luclin?). So I decide to ask for him to sell, and divide my split. Ok, I'm sure you can all see it coming ~ &quot;Well, you didn't fight with us the whole time, so you don't deserve a share.&quot;<br>Well crud. Now I've fought for an hour in HHK, and have absolutely no loot to show for it. On the bright side I did get XP, which was what I was really after, but hey ~ there are always better things to buy, and I still need to save up for some Acrylia armor <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>After my experience with him, I have taken to doing a little shout, whenever we happen to be in the same zone. No, I don't follow him around (he seems to be ANON a lot lately anyways) but I do have him in my /friends list, and I have a macro to tell me if he happens to be in the same zone I do. I also have my little shout on a macro.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usliver123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sliver123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Political Piggies</span><br>  Posts: 167<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/24/02 8:51:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1069.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My experience with Srir</span><hr size=1> PERSONAL ATTACK! Quick Veloxia, call the feds. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufroscheto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Froscheto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/24/02 9:07:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1069.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My experience with Srir</span><hr size=1> sounds like a shady character to me =/ <p>Froscheto<br>Wizard of Agnosticism (...)<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=308109>Magelo Profile, thing.</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=audaciti>Audaciti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><b